### Description

According to mat menu docs:

> "The menu is attached to and opened via application of the matMenuTriggerFor directive"

The mat-menu-panel should be attached to it's trigger but when the trigger is absolute within a scrollable container, the mat menu doesn't scroll with the container and only scrolls with the entire window.


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
Have a component with a scrollable container. Within this container have a mat menu trigger with position absolute. It's container has position relative. Scroll container -> trigger stays in the right position and scrolls away but the mat menu panel stays in the same position relative to the window.
https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-5hrato


